reviews.text: Pretty much just a place for a coffee or yum cha, and maybe buy a few stuff after work too
A very small mall connected to Sheung Wan mtr station. Good and convenient location. Bus stops for buses going to different places are just in front of the mall.
The mall is nothing special but very useful to access bridge to IFC and Macau Ferry.
Useful shops.. love MiniSo & Pret. Very friendly staff. We had a baby stroller so 1 staff member assisted me to service lift and was very helpful.

Personally I like this small shopping plaza, but it's not really a place to go shopping. There's a coffee shop, 7eleven and some small gift shops, besides a couple of restaurants. That is the extent of it. Facilities are clean and it connects directly into Sheung Wan MTR station and the walking bridge to IFC Mall as well as the Rumsey Street Parking Garage, so that's a plus. Staff are friendly but there is no real info desk.
